story.description: Annie Walker  is a single woman in her mid 30s, living in Milwaukee, Wisconsin. After her bakery failed, she lost her boyfriend and all of her savings, and now works in a jewelers store selling engagement rings. Although her flaky mother  encourages her to return home, Annie rents a bedroom from British immigrant Gil  and his lazy overweight sister Brynn . She has a sexual no-strings-attached relationship with the self-absorbed Ted  but hopes for something more. Only her friendship with Lillian Donovan  keeps her sane.
